<img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nCJXCEv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OwuDI36.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fmRrfDP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NAnV5lY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uKq5LaX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/71di1C9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gRIeAvl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XYAGiuQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9ucZFlx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My dog has recently taken to sleeping here in the garden. This is also where the previous owner’s dog’s ashes were buried about 7 years ago. I don’t know how but she seems to know that this is a sacred spot, a quiet spot. A spot for sniffing flowers and enjoying the grass while we can.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/GstYRPR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[iwasthinkingaboutsoup]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>One upside to having ADHD is that you gain a new hobby/obsession every week! Here are some of mine:</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XkZTx6m</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/c1kTG4X.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Post apocalyptic cosplay will always have a dirty place in my heart</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gRPErK4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I love to draw and I was blown away when an Imgurian recently reached out to buy a tattoo commission from me! My art is going to be on someone's body forever!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wd7rPB8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My last secret Santa where I made a viking style set of coasters and drinking horn holster. Leather work is probably my most rewarding passion.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fGrqZVX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I try my best at baking but it is definitely a science. Here's a Portal cake replica I made for a birthday party.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Uc6WArZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Probably my SO's favorite of my hobbies. Understandable since they get to eat the rejects AND the winners.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tl3nCZH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Bartender by trade. Edible art is great when you can see the transition of happiness in people when they get to taste your concoctions.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VRs8jdt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I love to grow plants and mushrooms alike! I had to fill my home with greenery since I live in the desert.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sC69Rnh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Needle felting for when I feel like making cute tiny things. I made a replica of my axolotl</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kvyB0hy.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Camping is an essential break from the dread I start to feel when work and too many horrible news stories start to pile up. 5/7 would recommend.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tAr8yv4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Valley Of Fire State Park, NV. One of my top 3 favorite places to go.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UB0cQR4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Hammy the axolotl tax!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XkZTx6m</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LANAAAAAAAAAA]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Vote!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/niw8GYN</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CG10MYh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This the line for my school board voting tonight.  There are some crazy guys trying to take over the board to push a religious/right wing agenda in our public school.  This is happening all across our country.  Resist!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/niw8GYN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bullheadbelly]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Freedom from religion</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/PFpOjSp</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/znr8xvX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/PFpOjSp</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Maitrify]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>How college admissions work</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6phRsO1</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9N6euXx.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6phRsO1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[vidadobl6]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>English major. Andrew Rudick</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/h6RP3RO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fmBy5SK.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></descripti